Kang Seung-yoon (Korean: 강승윤; born (1994-01-21)January 21, 1994), known mononymously as Seungyoon or Yoon, is a South Korean singer-songwriter, actor, and leader of boy group Winner.
Appearing on the reality television singing contest Superstar K2 (2010), he rose to prominence after finishing in fourth place.

In January 2011, he was scouted by South Korean label YG Entertainment and officially debuted as a solo artist in July 2013 with the digital single "It Rains" (비가 온다) and as the leader of Winner in August 2014.
